issues.title: Engine Oil Consumption Issues
issues.description: Excessive oil consumption reported in the 4.0L naturally aspirated engine, with some owners reporting consumption rates of 1 quart per 1,000-2,000 miles
symptoms: Frequent need to add oil between services
issues.fix_description: Engine inspection, potential piston ring or valve seal replacement if excessive consumption confirmed
issues.prevention: Regular oil level monitoring, use recommended oil grade, avoid extended oil change intervals

issues.title: PDK Transmission Jerky Shifting
issues.description: PDK dual-clutch transmission experiencing rough or jerky shifts, particularly during low-speed maneuvers and parking situations
issues.fix_description: Software update, clutch adaptation reset, or clutch pack replacement in severe cases
issues.prevention: Regular transmission service, proper break-in procedure, avoid aggressive low-speed driving

issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing
issues.description: PCM (Porsche Communication Management) system experiencing random freezes, black screens, and unresponsive touchscreen
issues.fix_description: Software update, system reset, or PCM unit replacement if hardware failure confirmed
issues.prevention: Keep system updated, avoid using system during extreme temperatures

issues.title: Rear Main Seal Oil Leak
issues.description: Oil leakage from rear main seal causing oil spots under vehicle and potential clutch contamination
issues.fix_description: Engine removal and rear main seal replacement
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes, avoid overfilling oil, monitor for early signs of leakage

issues.title: Carbon Fiber Interior Trim Cracking
issues.description: Carbon fiber interior trim pieces developing hairline cracks and delamination, particularly around high-touch areas
symptoms: Visible cracks in carbon fiber trim
issues.fix_description: Replacement of affected trim pieces under warranty or aftermarket refinishing
issues.prevention: Avoid harsh cleaning chemicals, use UV protection, gentle cleaning methods

issues.title: Throttle Body Carbon Buildup
issues.description: Carbon deposits accumulating in throttle body causing rough idle, reduced performance, and engine hesitation
issues.fix_description: Throttle body cleaning and carbon deposit removal
issues.prevention: Regular high-RPM driving, quality fuel usage, periodic throttle body cleaning

issues.title: Convertible Top Motor Failure
issues.description: Electric motor for convertible top mechanism failing, preventing top operation and potentially leaving top stuck in intermediate position
issues.fix_description: Convertible top motor replacement and hydraulic system inspection
issues.prevention: Regular top operation, avoid forcing operation in cold weather, periodic lubrication

issues.title: Air Conditioning Compressor Clutch Failure
issues.description: A/C compressor clutch failing prematurely, resulting in loss of air conditioning function
issues.fix_description: A/C compressor clutch replacement or full compressor replacement if internal damage occurred
issues.prevention: Regular A/C system use, proper refrigerant levels, annual A/C service

issues.title: Fuel Pump High Pressure Sensor Failure
issues.description: High pressure fuel pump sensor failure causing fuel delivery issues, potential stalling, and check engine lights
issues.fix_description: High pressure fuel pump sensor replacement and system pressure testing
issues.prevention: Use quality fuel, replace fuel filter as scheduled, avoid running on low fuel

issues.title: Parking Brake Module Malfunction
issues.description: Electronic parking brake system experiencing intermittent failures, warning lights, and inability to engage or release
issues.fix_description: Parking brake actuator motor replacement or control module reprogramming
issues.prevention: Regular brake system maintenance, avoid forcing operation, periodic calibration

editorial.tagline: Pure flat-six symphony meets mid-engine perfection
editorial.hero_blurb: The 718 Boxster GTS 4.0 delivers everything purists demanded: a naturally aspirated flat-six engine in Porsche's most balanced chassis. This is the roadster that reclaimed the soul of the Boxster lineage.
editorial.essence: Porsche answered enthusiast prayers by dropping their iconic 4.0L flat-six into the perfectly balanced mid-engine 718 platform. The result is a naturally aspirated masterpiece that combines modern refinement with old-school character.
editorial.heritage: Born from the legendary 718 race cars of the 1950s-60s, the modern 718 Boxster carries forward Porsche's mid-engine roadster DNA. The GTS 4.0 represents the pinnacle of this lineage, restoring the flat-six heartbeat that defines Porsche's racing heritage.
editorial.design_philosophy: Porsche's designers focused on functional beauty, creating muscular haunches that house the wider track, aggressive front splitters for aerodynamic purpose, and subtle GTS badging that whispers rather than shouts its performance intentions.
editorial.motorsport_history: While not a direct racing derivative, the 718 platform shares fundamental mid-engine principles with Porsche's most successful race cars, from the original 718 RSK to modern GT4 Clubsport racers.
editorial.engine_character: The 4.0L flat-six is pure emotion incarnate - linear power delivery that builds to a crescendo at 7,800 RPM, with that unmistakable Porsche boxer rumble that turbocharging could never replicate.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 6-speed manual offers precise, mechanical engagement with perfectly weighted throws, while the 7-speed PDK delivers lightning-fast shifts that complement the engine's rev-happy nature.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Mid-engine balance creates supernatural agility with predictable, confidence-inspiring handling that rewards both spirited driving and track work. The chassis talks to you through every input.
editorial.steering_feel: Hydraulic-assisted steering provides genuine feedback and perfect weighting, allowing you to feel exactly what the front wheels are doing while maintaining modern refinement.
editorial.brake_confidence: Powerful, fade-resistant brakes with excellent pedal feel and modulation. The braking system matches the chassis' capabilities with confidence-inspiring stopping power.
editorial.sound_signature: A spine-tingling flat-six symphony that builds from a purposeful idle rumble to a screaming 7,800 RPM crescendo, with pops and crackles on overrun that never get old.
editorial.ideal_owner: Driving purists who want modern reliability wrapped in analog soul, weekend canyon carvers, and track day enthusiasts who appreciate naturally aspirated excellence over raw numbers.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Daily commuters in stop-and-go traffic, those prioritizing straight-line acceleration over handling balance, or buyers seeking maximum cargo space and practicality.
editorial.buyers_summary: The 718 Boxster GTS 4.0 represents the sweet spot of modern Porsche engineering. Buy the cleanest example you can afford, as these naturally aspirated gems will only become more desirable with time.

expertReviews.title: 2024 Porsche 718 Boxster GTS 4.0 Review - Nearly Perfect ...
pros: Excellent 4.0L naturally aspirated flat-6 engine
Outstanding technical competence and precision
Sharp front end and precise EPS steering
Excellent build quality and premium interior
Perfect throttle response and cohesive inputs
cons: Very long gearing limits fun factor
Lacks emotional connection despite technical excellence
Over $100k price tag reduces value proposition
JCR exhaust setup creates drone for daily driving
Too perfect and composed - lacks character
expertReviews.verdict: Technically brilliant but emotionally detached. The 718 Boxster GTS 4.0 delivers exceptional performance and build quality but feels too perfect to be truly engaging. At $100-110k, older 981 or 991.1 models offer better value and more character.

expertReviews.title: 2024 Porsche 718 Boxster GTS 4.0: Perfection On Four Wheels
pros: Exceptional 4.0L flat-six engine sound and performance
Outstanding steering feel and handling balance
Excellent PDK transmission with sport response mode
Impressive fuel economy (30-32 mpg highway)
Surprisingly good storage space with front and rear trunks
Old-school driving experience with modern performance
cons: Dated interior technology and small infotainment screen
Very expensive at $117,490 as tested
Long transmission gearing limits ability to enjoy engine revs
No wireless Apple CarPlay, still uses USB-A
End of the line before electric replacement
expertReviews.verdict: Despite costing $117,490, the 718 Boxster GTS 4.0 delivers an exceptional driving experience that justifies its price. The naturally aspirated 4.0L flat-six sounds incredible and the handling is perfectly balanced. While the interior tech is dated, the pure driving dynamics make this reviewer's top choice for sports cars if money were no object. It's the last of its kind before going electric.

expertReviews.title: 718 Boxster GTS 4.0L | Test Drive Review (#9)
pros: Naturally aspirated 4.0L flat-6 engine with 394 hp sounds much better than previous turbo 4-cylinder
Phenomenal handling with go-kart-like responsiveness at only 3200 lbs
Excellent brake feel with 13.8-inch carbon ceramic rotors
More interior comfort and storage space than expected for a compact 2-seater
Bose audio system provides excellent sound quality for under $1000 upgrade
cons: Six-figure price tag makes it expensive for entry-level Porsche
Very limited interior storage space with flimsy cup holder design
Racing yellow paint makes it a 'cop magnet'
Exhaust note can become wearing on longer drives
No wireless charging pad or dedicated phone storage
expertReviews.verdict: The 718 Boxster GTS 4.0 represents the last of its kind as Porsche's final all-ICE Boxster. While the six-figure price challenges its role as an 'entry-level' Porsche, the return of the naturally aspirated flat-6 engine addresses enthusiast complaints about the previous turbo 4-cylinder. The car delivers exceptional handling dynamics and driving engagement, though storage limitations and the high price point raise questions about value.

expertReviews.title: Best Sports Car in the World!? Porsche Boxster GTS 4.0 | 4k
pros: 400hp naturally aspirated flat-6 engine
Exceptional handling and steering feel
No scuttle shake despite being convertible
Great soundtrack and driving engagement
Perfect balance - not overly planted like GT3
Manual transmission with excellent auto-blip
Lightweight and efficient (35mpg possible)
Strong residual values
cons: Long gearing especially in 1st and 2nd gear
Uncomfortable 18-way sport seats
Short 6th gear for highway cruising
High RPM at motorway speeds
Limited modern features compared to competitors
Expensive starting at Â£80,000
expertReviews.verdict: The 718 Boxster GTS 4.0 is described as the better pure driver's car compared to BMW Z4 M40i, offering unmatched engagement and connection to the road. While it has comfort and practicality shortcomings, it excels as a sports car tool. Reviewer strongly recommends buying one before the electric replacement arrives, noting 400hp is more than enough for road use and praising its handling balance.

expertReviews.title: 2025 Porsche 718 Boxster GTS 4 0
pros: Exceptional steering feel and driver engagement
Lightweight at 3200 lbs with ideal balance
Outstanding six-speed manual transmission
Dual storage areas (9.7 cubic feet total)
Beautiful naturally aspirated 4.0L flat-six engine sound
One of the best driver's cars available
cons: Being discontinued after 2025 model year
Low ground clearance requires careful driving
Base model interior materials not premium for price point
Electric steering instead of hydraulic
expertReviews.verdict: The 2025 Porsche 718 Boxster GTS 4.0 represents one of the last great naturally aspirated sports cars, offering exceptional driver engagement through its lightweight design, superb manual transmission, and mid-engine balance. With 394 horsepower and weighing just 3200 lbs, it delivers the perfect combination of performance and handling. However, this is the final year before Porsche transitions to electric, making it a must-buy for driving enthusiasts who want one of the last true driver's cars.

expertReviews.title: Why I Walked Away | 2024 Porsche 718 Boxster GTS 4.0
pros: Excellent mid-engine balance and predictable handling
Great convertible with minimal weight penalty vs Cayman
Perfect steering calibration and input feel
Excellent PASM suspension system with good comfort and control
Strong naturally aspirated flat-6 engine with 394hp
Convertible top allows for open-air driving experience
cons: Long gear throws and excessive tilt in stock shifter
Aftermarket pedals make heel-toe more challenging than stock
Exhaust can be too loud for daily driving with sport mode
Limited practicality with mid-engine layout and two seats
Heavier wheels may reduce steering feedback
expertReviews.verdict: The 2024 Porsche 718 Boxster GTS 4.0 is a well-rounded sports car that offers the rare combination of convertible enjoyment without significant penalties in weight or rigidity compared to its Cayman sibling. With 394hp from its naturally aspirated flat-6, excellent balance, and superb modern Porsche input calibration, it makes for an excellent daily driver sports car. While it has some minor drawbacks like long shifter throws and practicality limitations, it's loved by many for being such a complete package.
